CONFORMANCE CLAIMS

Passing schema validation means a record is well-formed under JA-ES. It does
not establish conformance with the Judgment Assurance Minimum Control Standard,
which includes requirements no validator can test (see the specification,
"What the schema enforces, and what it cannot").

Do not represent validation results as "JA Certified," "Judgment Assurance
Certified," or as endorsement by Judgment Assurance Institute, LLC. Use of
these marks in connection with certification, assessment, or formal compliance
claims requires separate written authorization.

